      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Making deep learning go brrrr from first principles (2022)",
      "url": "https://horace.io/brrr_intro.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48246889",
      "score": 159,
      "comments": 59,
      "author": "tosh",
      "published": "2026-05-23T11:50:22Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Modern GPUs are heavily memory-bandwidth bound; optimizing deep learning requires reducing HBM-to-SRAM transfers, not just maximizing raw FLOPs.",
        "Kernel fusion is critical to bypass memory bottlenecks by combining element-wise operations into single GPU execution steps.",
        "Understanding hardware limits (SRAM vs. HBM) explains why compiler frameworks like PyTorch Inductor rely on automated fusion for speedups."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
