      "title": "A new suite of modern tools coming for editing and publishing RFCs",
      "url": "https://www.ietf.org/blog/new-tools-coming-for-editing-and-publishing-rfcs/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/luyrv4",
      "score": 16,
      "comments": 3,
      "author": "jmillikin",
      "published": "2026-05-23T07:53:07Z",
      "bullets": [
        "IETF transitions to XML v3 vocabulary (RFC 7991), enabling richer semantic web layouts, SVG diagrams, and accessible HTML outputs.",
        "Modern RFC pipelines leverage GitHub actions, Markdown-based authoring via `kramdown-rfc2629`, and the automated Python-based `xml2rfc` compiler.",
        "Web-based authoring templates, CLI syntax checkers, and official renderers streamline the workflow from initial draft to final TXT and PDF."
      ]
    },
    {
